  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema",
  "$id": "https://example.com/user-registration-schema.json",
  "title": "User Registration Schema",
  "description": "A schema to validate user registration forms",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["first_name", "last_name", "email", "password"],
  "properties": {
    "first_name": {
      "type": "string",
      "required": true,
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 255
    },
    "last_name": {
      "type": "string",
      "required": true,
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 255
    },
    "email": {
      "type": "string",
      "required": true,
      "email": true
    },
    "password": {
      "type": "string",
      "required": true,
      "minLength": 8,
      "maxLength": 255
    }
  },
  "patternProperties": {
    "^[a-z0-9]+$": {
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 32
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
```

This schema defines a user registration form that consists of the following required fields: `first_name`, `last_name`, `email`, and `password`. It also includes a nested object `address` with the following properties: `address_line1`, `address_line2`, `city`, `state`, and `postal_code`. The `address` object has a nested object `city` with a minimum length of 3 and a maximum length of 255 characters. The `password` property is a string with a minimum length of 8 characters and a maximum length of 255 characters.

The `patternProperties` pattern matches the first_name and last_name properties to the `^[a-z0-9]+$` regular expression. The password property uses the `^[a-z0-9]+$` regular expression to validate the minimum length and maximum length.

The `additionalProperties` property is set to `false`, which means that any additional properties beyond the required ones will be disallowed.

